<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF696AD6F835948B18FCBF4C" pageId="146" pageNumber="907" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF696AD6F835948B18FCBF4C" blockId="146.[1987,2588,613,1031]" lastBlockId="146.[1381,2587,1038,2019]" pageId="146" pageNumber="907">
Traditionally considered a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF696AD6F83694A3162DB829" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1842" box="[1994,2093,762,795]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="146" pageNumber="907" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Murina</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF696AD6F7BD94A316B2B829" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1915" box="[2113,2226,762,795]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Harpiola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="146" pageNumber="907" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Harpiola</taxonomicName>
is now tentatively treated as a distinct genus, based on morphology, following the discovery of more specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF696AD6F8089529166BB8A3" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1872" box="[2036,2155,880,913]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="146" pageNumber="907" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="grisea">H. grisea</taxonomicName>
in Mizoram and of a second species, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF696AD6F7C195F916BAB88B" box="[2109,2234,928,953]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Harpiola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="146" pageNumber="907" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="isodon">H. isodon</taxonomicName>
, in 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF696AD6F70D95F91751B88B" box="[2289,2385,928,953]" name="Taiwan" pageId="146" pageNumber="907">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF696AD6F66795F91413B88B" box="[2459,2579,928,953]" name="Vietnam" pageId="146" pageNumber="907">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
; nevertheless, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF696AD6F77395E61700B8D2" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1915" box="[2191,2304,959,992]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Harpiola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="146" pageNumber="907" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Harpiola</taxonomicName>
is phylogenetically imbedded within 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF696AD6F73995BF1729BF35" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1842" box="[2245,2345,998,1031]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="146" pageNumber="907" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Murina</taxonomicName>
and may be best retained there; further study needed. The Mizoram specimens resemble 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF696AD6F6B1925717C6BF1D" box="[2381,2502,1038,1071]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Harpiola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="146" pageNumber="907" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="isodon">H. isodon</taxonomicName>
in fur coloration; further sampling throughout both species’ ranges is needed to understand the full variability. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
